This paper deals with robotic grasping controllers and visual servoing, which are both topics within the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper specifically focuses on the use of RGB-D cameras and image-based visual servoing, which are subtopics within computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to predict image feature coordinates, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's application to grasping moving objects involves control systems (cs.SY).
